The launching ceremony for the [MASK] with triple winds took place in the city council’s chamber.

In August 1957, the Seoul Metropolitan Council passed "The Seoul Metropolitan Ordinances to Install a City-Run Orchestra", the Naval Symphony Orchestra became the Seoul Philharmonic Orchestra, the first Korean [MASK] funded by a government.

After a subscription concert in the Seoul Civic Hall on June 25, 1950, the [MASK] had to suspend its activities due to the outbreak of the Korean War, but resumed performance with the name of the Naval Symphony Orchestra, just five months later, to soothe the broken hearts of Koreans during the war.
